      "content": "While ibuprofen is sometimes used for headaches, anti-inflammatory NSAIDs like it can be dangerous for people with kidney disease because they strain the kidneys. Even if your kidneys have been stable recently, a healthcare professional should approve its use to ensure it does not harm your health during this acute episode. You should contact your doctor or pharmacist immediately to discuss whether this specific medication is safe for you right now. Your safety is the most important priority, so please do not take it without their explicit guidance.",
