      "content": "That assumption is risky; even a one-time dose of NSAIDs like ibuprofen can significantly impact kidney function in people with chronic kidney disease, potentially causing acute injury. Taking 200mg without verification could lead to further harm you wouldn't witness until the damage is already done. Please consult your pharmacist or doctor quickly, as they can advise you on the safest and most effective treatment for your immediate symptoms. Your long-term health depends on strict adherence to medical safety guidelines, not just trying to get through the day.",
